on circumstantial evidence is dangerous.

72
00:06:25,451 --> 00:06:28,521
You know Article 307
of the Criminal Procedure Code, right?

73
00:06:28,588 --> 00:06:33,593
"Facts should be based
on relevant evidence."

74
00:06:34,560 --> 00:06:36,162
We need direct evidence.

75
00:06:44,737 --> 00:06:46,606
Does the prosecution
have anything else to say?

76
00:06:48,708 --> 00:06:53,212
Counsel pointed out
something very important.

77
00:06:54,480 --> 00:06:58,918
Facts should be based
on direct evidence, where possible.

78
00:07:00,186 --> 00:07:02,255
I overlooked that.

79
00:07:03,356 --> 00:07:04,424
So...

80
00:07:07,860 --> 00:07:09,962
If counsel allows it,

81
00:07:10,129 --> 00:07:13,800
I would like to bring the victim
as a witness.

82
00:07:15,334 --> 00:07:17,236
But she's unconscious.

83
00:07:18,805 --> 00:07:20,306
She woke up this morning.

84
00:07:20,573 --> 00:07:24,944
I didn't bring her as a witness
because I didn't think it would be needed.

85
00:07:26,379 --> 00:07:29,415
