254
00:20:18,383 --> 00:20:20,852
Your defense was impressive.

255
00:20:22,487 --> 00:20:24,690
So don't beat yourself up.

256
00:20:25,857 --> 00:20:27,359
You did pretty well...

257
00:20:29,228 --> 00:20:30,529
for a public defender.

258
00:20:37,903 --> 00:20:40,239
Hey, you! You!

259
00:20:43,809 --> 00:20:45,043
Don't you remember me?

260
00:20:46,578 --> 00:20:48,780
It's that lady.

261
00:20:49,715 --> 00:20:54,019
You threw our ball into the road
and it got ruined.

262
00:20:54,486 --> 00:20:55,554
Remember?

263
00:21:03,228 --> 00:21:04,296
I don't remember.

264
00:21:07,566 --> 00:21:08,900
So you're running away.

265
00:21:11,169 --> 00:21:13,272
Hey, stop right there!

266
00:21:14,106 --> 00:21:15,340
Hey!

267
00:21:17,376 --> 00:21:19,845
-Where are you going?
-Stop!

268
00:21:19,911 --> 00:21:21,013
Hey!

269
00:21:32,090 --> 00:21:33,959
Where are you going to go now?

270
00:21:34,526 --> 00:21:36,161
You're in trouble now.

271
00:21:40,732 --> 00:21:44,836
You crawled your way
into the perfect spot.

272
00:21:45,170 --> 00:21:49,508
Hey, you guys. I could sue you for this.

273
00:21:49,741 --> 00:21:51,910
If you even touch me,
it will be assault and battery.

274
00:21:52,144 --> 00:21:55,447
It's at night
and there are several of you.

275
00:21:56,281 --> 00:21:58,050
So there could be additional punishment.

276
00:22:05,090 --> 00:22:07,793
Hey. Stalker.

277
00:22:08,260 --> 00:22:09,428
"Stalker"?

278
00:22:12,698 --> 00:22:14,966
Please call the police.

279
00:22:15,133 --> 00:22:17,436
Or go get some people.

280
00:22:17,569 --> 00:22:20,372
Promise me something.
Then I'll get rid of them.

281
00:22:21,139 --> 00:22:22,207
Promise what?

282
00:22:22,374 --> 00:22:24,409
Promise you won't give up on Seong-bin.

283
00:22:24,509 --> 00:22:26,778
Why are you talking about that here?

284
00:22:27,979 --> 00:22:29,314
I won't give up.

285
00:22:31,183 --> 00:22:32,184
Never.

286
00:22:34,419 --> 00:22:36,955
I wasn't going to give up on her.

287
00:22:39,091 --> 00:22:41,193
What are they talking about?

288
00:22:41,693 --> 00:22:45,530
Hey, look at me.
Don't you get this situation?

289
00:22:45,630 --> 00:22:48,066
You were talking to me.

290
00:22:50,235 --> 00:22:52,671
Come over here.

291
00:22:52,938 --> 00:22:55,807
Who are you? You come here, you bastard.

292
00:22:55,974 --> 00:22:56,975
Hey, hold it.

293
00:22:59,311 --> 00:23:01,747
That is Park Su-ha.

294
00:23:02,180 --> 00:23:04,349
Chung-gi got beat up by him.

295
00:23:04,516 --> 00:23:07,386
You know, Kim Chung-gi,
our local taekwondo representative.

296
00:23:07,819 --> 00:23:08,820
My back hurts.

297
00:23:08,987 --> 00:23:12,958
-Are you sure?
-Yes, I saw it myself.

298
00:23:14,493 --> 00:23:16,194
Hey, stop right there.

299
00:23:16,528 --> 00:23:19,231
We would love to talk to you right now.

300
00:23:20,499 --> 00:23:22,834
But it's kind of late.

301
00:23:23,268 --> 00:23:25,070
We have to go attend classes.

302
00:23:25,203 --> 00:23:28,073
So let's talk another time.

303
00:23:31,109 --> 00:23:34,246
No. I want to talk right now.

304
00:23:34,479 --> 00:23:37,983
I would love to do that,
but we just don't have the time.

305
00:23:38,316 --> 00:23:40,652
We have to go attend classes.

306
00:23:46,258 --> 00:23:47,993
-Hey, wait for me.
-Hey.

307
00:23:49,394 --> 00:23:51,129
I have nothing against you.

308
00:23:53,365 --> 00:23:55,033
I never had anything against you.

309
00:24:03,408 --> 00:24:06,411
-Is that it?
-Don't forget your promise.

310
00:24:06,511 --> 00:24:08,447
Take care of Seong-bin until the end.

311
00:24:08,680 --> 00:24:12,284
Hey. You didn't do anything.

312
00:24:18,990 --> 00:24:21,626
So Dong-hui fell after hanging
from the windowsill?

313
00:24:21,960 --> 00:24:24,396
-Yes.
-Why was she hanging there?

314
00:24:24,563 --> 00:24:26,131
There wasn't anyone in the classroom.

315
00:24:26,665 --> 00:24:30,469
I'm not sure, I wanted to find out more,
but it was too chaotic.

316
00:24:32,103 --> 00:24:34,272
So she fell
after hanging from the windowsill.

317
00:24:35,640 --> 00:24:39,444
How do I prove that?
Shall I call Dong-hui back to court?

318
00:24:40,378 --> 00:24:43,515
No, but what if she lies again?

319
00:24:44,015 --> 00:24:46,117
I have to find evidence.

320
00:24:48,553 --> 00:24:50,889
I really thought
you had given up on Seong-bin.

321
00:24:51,056 --> 00:24:54,292
Shut it. I didn't decide not to give up
because of you.

322
00:24:55,861 --> 00:24:56,995
Go on in.

323
00:25:00,265 --> 00:25:01,566
Hey, Stalker.

324
00:25:04,870 --> 00:25:07,172
You didn't really save me.

325
00:25:09,074 --> 00:25:10,609
So I'm only kind of grateful.

326
00:25:24,756 --> 00:25:28,627
How did he know where I live?

327
00:25:39,170 --> 00:25:40,605
It's "I'll be there" again.

328
00:25:43,475 --> 00:25:44,543
No way.

329
00:25:58,590 --> 00:26:03,662
Oh my gosh. It must be him.

330
00:26:11,303 --> 00:26:14,973
You can use road-view maps
instead of crime-scene photos.

331
00:26:15,040 --> 00:26:16,575
They do it a lot at trials.

332
00:26:16,641 --> 00:26:18,443
I see.

333
00:26:18,810 --> 00:26:20,845
That way you will do less legwork.

334
00:26:20,979 --> 00:26:22,981
You were going to go straight
to the crime scene, right?

335
00:26:23,281 --> 00:26:24,349
Yes.

336
00:26:29,721 --> 00:26:34,059
I must prove Ko Seong-bin is innocent
in this trial.

337
00:26:34,225 --> 00:26:36,227
-Help me.
-I don't want to.

338
00:26:36,828 --> 00:26:38,830
Why should I help you?

339
00:26:45,804 --> 00:26:47,806
The victim's testimony is all they have
as evidence.

340
00:26:47,872 --> 00:26:50,008
But the victim keeps lying.

341
00:26:50,275 --> 00:26:52,877
-What should I do when...
-My gosh, the battery is dead.

342
00:26:53,378 --> 00:26:57,882
My hearing aid is out.
I can't hear anything now.

343
00:27:04,489 --> 00:27:07,425
I'm sorry for being impudent.
Please help me.

344
00:27:14,966 --> 00:27:17,636
I will be responsible
for your coffee from now on.

345
00:27:21,940 --> 00:27:23,141
I'LL PESTER YOU UNTIL YOU HELP ME

346
00:27:23,208 --> 00:27:24,109
I'LL DO MY BEST

347
00:27:24,175 --> 00:27:25,443
PLEASE HELP ME THIS ONCE

348
00:27:25,744 --> 00:27:27,612
Enough.

349
00:27:29,447 --> 00:27:30,448
Where do you...

350
00:27:34,052 --> 00:27:36,855
Shall I help you instead?

351
00:27:37,188 --> 00:27:40,258
I was famous for field investigation
in my police days.

352
00:27:40,325 --> 00:27:41,626
Forget it!

353
00:27:48,333 --> 00:27:49,300
Gosh.

354
00:27:49,668 --> 00:27:51,269
And used up all my Post-its to boot.

355
00:27:52,437 --> 00:27:54,305
That was so distracting.

356
00:28:02,514 --> 00:28:04,049
How are you going to help?

357
00:28:06,418 --> 00:28:10,188
I have the tricks and know-how
that I developed as a police officer.

358
00:28:11,956 --> 00:28:14,125
Are these your tricks and know-how?

359
00:28:16,361 --> 00:28:19,431
We have to get inside the lives
of the victim and defendant.

360
00:28:19,531 --> 00:28:22,467
They're both students,
so we need to start at the school.

361
00:28:23,234 --> 00:28:25,804
You should go and talk to the students.

362
00:28:25,870 --> 00:28:28,606
I will go and investigate the crime scene.

363
00:28:41,286 --> 00:28:45,790
Seong-bin is unbelievable.
She swore in court, too.

364
00:28:45,857 --> 00:28:49,594
That lawyer is hopeless.
How can she say she's innocent?

365
00:28:49,661 --> 00:28:50,929
How can she do that?

366
00:28:51,429 --> 00:28:53,732
-She's a monster.
-I know.

367
00:28:53,865 --> 00:28:56,835
-That is so totally foolish.
-I know.

368
00:28:59,804 --> 00:29:01,439
Who are you?

369
00:29:03,675 --> 00:29:09,748
Yello, friends.
I'm Jang Ye-ri, a new student.

370
00:29:12,083 --> 00:29:14,018
Seong-bin led in picking on Dong-hui?

371
00:29:14,085 --> 00:29:17,489
That's right. She's the one
who made the nickname "Double Nose."

372
00:29:17,789 --> 00:29:20,925
Why did she pick on her?
What did Dong-hui do wrong?

373
00:29:21,626 --> 00:29:23,428
What did she do wrong?

374
00:29:23,895 --> 00:29:27,932
She is just too perfect.
She was too pretty for her own good.

375
00:29:28,066 --> 00:29:29,768
She had good grades, too.

376
00:29:29,968 --> 00:29:32,971
She got a full scholarship,
and started school two years early.

377
00:29:33,505 --> 00:29:36,975
So did you take part
in picking on Dong-hui?

378
00:29:37,509 --> 00:29:41,613
It's not like that.
But we would get picked on if we didn't.

379
00:30:09,474 --> 00:30:13,678
Did Dong-hui say that
she didn't want to live?

380
00:30:13,945 --> 00:30:17,582
Of course not. She got into that agency.

381
00:30:18,616 --> 00:30:20,819
What did she do during breaks?
I heard she had no friends.

382
00:30:20,985 --> 00:30:24,989
She would play the piano
or study in the computer room.

383
00:30:25,456 --> 00:30:26,691
The computer room?

384
00:30:28,793 --> 00:30:29,894
What is this?

385
00:31:08,099 --> 00:31:12,070
How do I find the computer
that Mun Dong-hui used?

386
00:31:16,774 --> 00:31:19,143
This is the one that Mun Dong-hui used.

387
00:31:19,310 --> 00:31:20,411
Really?

388
00:31:22,780 --> 00:31:24,249
When did you come?

389
00:31:31,289 --> 00:31:33,491
I know. I'm embarrassed, too.

390
00:31:34,492 --> 00:31:36,995
I'll take care of things. You can go now.

391
00:31:47,538 --> 00:31:51,142
I've turned it on. What should I do now?

392
00:31:51,676 --> 00:31:54,345
What are you doing?
Can't you find internet history?

393
00:31:54,612 --> 00:31:55,647
Of course I do.

394
00:31:55,780 --> 00:32:00,652
"Find the internet history"?
Isn't that what hackers do?

395
00:32:16,301 --> 00:32:17,502
SEARCH HISTORY

396
00:32:19,304 --> 00:32:22,874
Wow, awesome. All the details are here.

397
00:32:22,974 --> 00:32:24,909
COMPUTER ROOM DAILY LOG
THURSDAY, MAY 24, MUN DONG-HUI

398
00:32:24,976 --> 00:32:26,978
Look at the records
between 2:00 to 3:00 p.m. on the 24th.

399
00:32:27,045 --> 00:32:27,979
Okay.

400
00:32:30,214 --> 00:32:32,617
Hey, why are you bossing me around?

401
00:32:33,251 --> 00:32:36,854
This is the computer usage record.
Dong-hui's usage time is all here.

402
00:32:37,088 --> 00:32:38,122
Really?

403
00:32:40,625 --> 00:32:42,160
I'll take care of it.

404
00:32:43,661 --> 00:32:46,264
Look at this. The search words are odd.

405
00:32:47,432 --> 00:32:48,599
What?

406
00:32:52,937 --> 00:32:54,973
GETTING RID OF CIGARETTE SMELL
HOW TO BUY CIGARETTES ONLINE

407
00:32:55,039 --> 00:32:58,176
Wasn't Dong-hui a model student?
Wasn't she about to debut, too?

408
00:32:58,843 --> 00:33:01,112
-Yes.
-So why would she look this up?

409
00:33:01,946 --> 00:33:06,351
Ms. Jjang, I found out
why Mun Dong-hui fell.

410
00:33:17,028 --> 00:33:20,064
You want me to go back and take the stand?

411
00:33:20,765 --> 00:33:21,766
Why?

412
00:33:22,867 --> 00:33:26,004
You lied last time,
so you should tell the truth.

413
00:33:27,572 --> 00:33:29,107
I didn't lie.

414
00:33:31,609 --> 00:33:32,977
You smoke, don't you?

415
00:33:35,546 --> 00:33:38,683
No. Why suddenly bring that up?

416
00:33:40,451 --> 00:33:43,388
I went to your school
and looked up your search history.

417
00:33:44,889 --> 00:33:47,592
"Cigarette vending machine location."
"How do minors buy cigarettes?"

418
00:33:47,658 --> 00:33:50,128
"Internet purchase of cigarettes."
"How to get rid of cigarette smell."

419
00:33:50,194 --> 00:33:51,763
"Cigarette-purchasing agents."

420
00:33:53,031 --> 00:33:54,132
And then...

421
00:33:56,734 --> 00:33:59,871
-This.
-How do you have...

422
00:34:01,406 --> 00:34:03,107
I went to your school today.

423
00:34:04,342 --> 00:34:06,511
Weren't you smoking that day?

424
00:34:06,811 --> 00:34:11,616
But Seong-bin came in, so you hid outside
the window and fell, right?

425
00:34:13,951 --> 00:34:17,288
I can sort of understand
why you lied on the stand.

426
00:34:17,455 --> 00:34:21,592
You're about to debut, so you're worried
about people knowing you smoke.

427
00:34:22,794 --> 00:34:25,563
But that's no reason
to ruin someone else's life.

428
00:34:28,433 --> 00:34:31,769
Let go of me!
I need to hear what that brat says.

429
00:34:31,836 --> 00:34:33,304
Stay here.

430
00:34:37,308 --> 00:34:39,043
Did you get the summons?

431
00:34:39,610 --> 00:34:41,312
Please come to the trial
at three tomorrow.

432
00:34:41,612 --> 00:34:45,216
Come and testify
that Seong-bin is innocent, okay?

433
00:34:46,350 --> 00:34:47,552
I don't want to.

434
00:34:48,586 --> 00:34:51,222
Mun Dong-hui, it's not about wanting to.

435
00:34:52,156 --> 00:34:54,525
No. I'm not going.

436
00:34:55,293 --> 00:34:57,095
Look at that freaking bitch...

437
00:34:59,964 --> 00:35:02,233
Hey, Double Nose. Let's talk.

438
00:35:02,300 --> 00:35:04,869
I told you to stay still.
What are you doing here?

439
00:35:05,103 --> 00:35:07,071
I'm just going to talk. Just talk.

440
00:35:08,739 --> 00:35:11,909
Let me ask you
why you're doing this to me.

441
00:35:12,310 --> 00:35:14,912
Is it just because
I called you "Double Nose"?

442
00:35:15,346 --> 00:35:17,215
Is that why you're doing this to me?

443
00:35:17,682 --> 00:35:18,850
"Just because"?

444
00:35:22,587 --> 00:35:25,623
Okay. Let me ask you.

445
00:35:26,624 --> 00:35:28,593
Why did you pick on me?

446
00:35:29,327 --> 00:35:30,328
What?

447
00:35:30,928 --> 00:35:33,331
What did I do to you that you tease me?

448
00:35:34,332 --> 00:35:36,968
What did I do to you that you outcast me?

449
00:35:39,570 --> 00:35:43,908
What did I do to you
that you put a rag in my lunch?

450
00:35:47,211 --> 00:35:49,313
What did I do to you?

451
00:35:50,715 --> 00:35:55,219
Why did you call my mother an idiot?

452
00:35:58,890 --> 00:36:01,659
-Hey, that's--
-Dong-hui.

453
00:36:02,293 --> 00:36:04,462
That's one thing. This is different.

454
00:36:04,629 --> 00:36:06,864
That's no reason to make her a murderer.

455
00:36:07,265 --> 00:36:10,401
Seong-bin could go to jail because of you.

456
00:36:10,468 --> 00:36:11,802
So, let her go.

457
00:36:12,837 --> 00:36:14,872
I've been living in a prison anyway.

458
00:36:16,474 --> 00:36:22,146
I lived in a prison she created.
And I didn't even know what I did.

459
00:36:23,314 --> 00:36:27,885
I didn't know why
or how long I had to be in there.

460
00:36:29,287 --> 00:36:31,355
I lived all alone like that.

461
00:36:34,025 --> 00:36:38,196
So let her go live in prison.

462
00:36:40,231 --> 00:36:42,033
With no friends.

463
00:36:43,701 --> 00:36:45,670
Or anyone on her side.

464
00:36:46,504 --> 00:36:48,406
She should live like that.

465
00:36:49,774 --> 00:36:50,942
Just like I did.

466
00:36:56,948 --> 00:37:02,887
My friends, my lawyer.
No one will believe me.

467
00:37:03,921 --> 00:37:05,523
What's the use of living?

468
00:37:07,525 --> 00:37:09,627
Will they believe me if I just die?

469
00:37:11,028 --> 00:37:12,763
Will they regret not believing me?

470
00:37:16,300 --> 00:37:19,070
Mun Dong-hui. That's no reason to--

471
00:37:19,604 --> 00:37:20,671
Let's go.

472
00:37:22,373 --> 00:37:25,776
What do you mean?
She is the only one who can...

473
00:37:26,410 --> 00:37:27,645
Let's just go.

474
00:37:29,614 --> 00:37:32,984
I'll be tried without Dong-hui.

475
00:37:34,585 --> 00:37:39,056
Of course, I could prove your innocence
without her.

476
00:37:39,924 --> 00:37:44,528
But we could lose. What will you do then?

477
00:37:47,398 --> 00:37:48,833
It can't be helped.

478
00:37:49,734 --> 00:37:50,835
What?

479
00:37:53,871 --> 00:37:55,039
I'm sorry.

480
00:37:56,874 --> 00:38:00,745
I know this may sound like an excuse,
but I did it because I was jealous.

481
00:38:02,213 --> 00:38:06,517
I think I lost it
when others joined in on it.

482
00:38:08,886 --> 00:38:11,289
I didn't know I was holding a stone
in my hand.

483
00:38:13,024 --> 00:38:17,795
And I didn't realize
a frog could die if I hit it.

484
00:38:21,132 --> 00:38:22,533
I'm really sorry.

485
00:38:35,212 --> 00:38:36,614
What will you do?

486
00:38:38,949 --> 00:38:41,085
You're the one
with the stone in your hand.

487
00:38:41,919 --> 00:38:45,289
Are you going to kill the frog
as Seong-bin did?

488
00:39:11,182 --> 00:39:14,452
What should we do?
What if Dong-hui doesn't come?

489
00:39:15,386 --> 00:39:18,456
-She'll come.
-Did you look into her mind?

490
00:39:20,624 --> 00:39:23,494
She said what she wanted to say
and heard what she wanted to hear.

491
00:39:23,894 --> 00:39:25,196
So, she'll come.

492
00:39:27,198 --> 00:39:29,500
Then I'm done here. Let's go.

493
00:39:36,707 --> 00:39:38,743
KO SEONG-BIN CASE FILE

494
00:39:42,813 --> 00:39:44,715
Here. Let me do that for you.

495
00:39:48,719 --> 00:39:49,820
Thank you.

496
00:39:55,559 --> 00:39:56,527
Ms. Jjang.

497
00:39:57,528 --> 00:40:00,164
You're going
into Seong-bin's trial, right?

498
00:40:01,565 --> 00:40:02,600
Yes.

499
00:40:06,036 --> 00:40:07,204
This is for you.

500
00:40:08,773 --> 00:40:10,107
Why are you...

501
00:40:13,377 --> 00:40:15,045
No. It's too much.

502
00:40:15,713 --> 00:40:18,416
It's just a small gift. Please take it.

503
00:40:18,949 --> 00:40:21,352
We're not close enough
to exchange such things.

504
00:40:21,852 --> 00:40:23,320
This is too fast.

505
00:40:25,689 --> 00:40:28,859
-What do you mean?
-Absolutely fast...

506
00:40:32,062 --> 00:40:33,230
What is this?

507
00:40:34,131 --> 00:40:35,299
